fox.title: FOX
fox.description: FOX broadcasting network has a 30-year legacy of innovative, hit programming delivering high-quality scripted, non-scripted and live content, as well as major sports. Fox Corporation is the parent company of Tubi.

573234.title: Gordon Ramsay's American Road Trip
573234.description: Strap in with the famously sharp-tongued chef and his foodie friends as they cruise across the country by RV for a uniquely American culinary tour.

672508.title: Lost Angeles: City of Homeless
672508.description: A deadly humanitarian crisis is exploding on the streets of LA: homelessness. As the problem grows, who's to blame and what's being done to solve it?

673651.title: TMZ Presents Johnny vs. Amber: From Love to Hate
673651.description: TMZ looks at how Johnny Depp and Amber Heard's relationship went from white-hot love to red-hot anger in this eye-opening special.

681633.title: Bridge
681633.description: This documentary chronicles the stories of some of the survivors who were on the I-35 Bridge in Minneapolis when it collapsed in 2007.

687678.title: TMZ Investigates: Who Really Killed Michael Jackson?
687678.description: TMZ dives into the King of Pop's final months, Dr. Conrad Murray's conviction for his death, and those who contributed to his substance abuse.

687701.title: TMZ Investigates: What Really Happened to Richard Simmons
687701.description: The tabloid site digs into the various theories and, in the end, finds an answer that explains why a man who was everywhere suddenly vanished.

689951.title: Academy of Country Music Honors Preview
689951.description: An evening filled with live music, tributes and performances from iconic country music artists.

707102.title: TMZ's Merry Elfin' Christmas
707102.description: This Christmas, some of the biggest names in entertainment take over TMZ to talk about the wildest and most memorable stories of 2022.

711653.title: TMZ Presents: Lamar Odom: Sex, Drugs & Kardashians
711653.description: NBA great Lamar Odom gets candid about his sex addiction, drug use and overdose—and how his downfall torpedoed his marriage to Khloe Kardashian.

722685.title: TMZ Investigates: Lisa Marie Presley: Unending Tragedy
722685.description: New details about Lisa Marie Presley's unforeseen passing are revealed.

100001599.title: TMZ Investigates: 9/11: The Fifth Plane
100001599.description: The all-new special TMZ Investigates: 9/11: The Fifth Plane investigates what could have been a fifth plane being targeted on 9/11.

0300009096.title: Don’t Forget the Lyrics
0300009096.description: Don't Forget the Lyrics challenges contestants' musical memory as they try to win $1 million by remembering a song and its lyrics.

0300008524.title: The Real Dirty Dancing
0300008524.description: Celebrities take on an all-new dance competition where they learn, rehearse, and execute classic movie dance scenes to see who the ultimate winner is.

04700.title: Crime Stories With Nancy Grace
04700.description: FOX Nation's Nancy Grace dives deep into the day's most shocking crimes and asks the tough questions with honest perspective you won't get anywhere else.

0300006542.title: Ana Polo Rules
0300006542.description: The lawyer and star of "Caso Cerrado” is your judge in this fascinating small claims case series, which is full of dramatic family disputes.

0300005831.title: Ultimate Tag
0300005831.description: Competitors must vault, dodge, tumble, and dive, as they make their way through several different, challenging, three-dimensional obstacle courses.

0300006189.title: Mental Samurai
0300006189.description: An obstacle course for the mind tests contestants' intelligence and mental agility; Rob Lowe hosts.

0300009670.title: HouseBroken
0300009670.description: "HouseBroken" is an irreverent animated series following a group of neighborhood animals who help each other navigate the complicated life of being a pet.

0300000069.title: Fox Sports College Basketball Classic: Mountain West
0300000069.description: Fox Sports College Basketball Classic: Mountain West

0300007794.title: TMZ Investigates: Tiger King - What Really Went Down?
0300007794.description: A behind-the-scenes look at the true-crime story involving Joe Exotic's murder-for-hire plot and the disappearance of Carole Baskin's husband.

0300006066.title: Saints and Sinners
0300006066.description: The Capshaws and the Martins have battled for generations in the Miami Beach hotel business.

0300009158.title: MasterChef Junior
0300009158.description: Talented children between the ages of 8 and 13 showcase their culinary abilities and passion for food through a series of delicious challenges.

0300008237.title: Gordon Ramsay's Road Trip
0300008237.description: Join renowned chef Gordon Ramsay as he hits the road for a hilarious culinary exploration with his pals Gino D'Acampo and Fred Sirieix.

0300005165.title: Divorce Court
0300005165.description: Judge Star Jones is the new face of Divorce Court presiding with her wisdom & experience. Join this new era through tears, laughter, truth & realness!

0300007851.title: Boardroom Chats
0300007851.description: When it comes to moving your career towards a high-level board position, the road can be tricky to navigate. This series explains the pitfalls.

04768.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds
04768.description: Part Three of the Emmy-winning series, written and directed by the late Carl Sagan’s wife and hosted by his protege, explores our wondrous universe.

04765.title: I Can See Your Voice
04765.description: Contestants compete to win a cash prize if they can tell the difference between good and bad singers, without ever hearing them sing.

0300006439.title: The Issue Is
0300006439.description: FOX’s Elex Michaelson hosts debates and conversations with newsmakers about political and controversial issues impacting California and the nation.

0300009735.title: Crockett's Corner
0300009735.description: In this series, Super Bowl Champion Ray Crockett gives a look into the minds of those in the sports industry, with a conversation beyond the lines.

0300007809.title: TMZ Investigates: UFOs: The Pentagon Proof
0300007809.description: Unpack the first-ever declassified Pentagon report detailing 144 accounts of UFO sightings, including new footage released from a USS naval ship.

0300005949.title: Wicked Wicked Games
0300005949.description: A woman whose husband left her for another woman with wealth 25 years ago plots her revenge to take him down in a way he won't soon forget.

0300005166.title: War Stories With Oliver North
0300005166.description: Documentary series featuring many overseas combat experiences of both the military forces and those citizens assisted, from WWII to 2005.

0300005245.title: Strange Inheritance
0300005245.description: From multi-million dollar treasures to bizarre collections, this series tells the stories of how families deal with their newly acquired possessions.

0300007971.title: Joe Millionaire
0300007971.description: When a 28-year old heavy equipment operator disguises himself as a millionaire, 20 hopeful young women jump at the chance to become his girlfriend.

0300005479.title: 25 Words or Less
0300005479.description: This raucous game show pits celebrities against civilians in a rapid-fire challenge where contestants get clues to guess secret words and phrases.

0300006502.title: Cherries Wild
0300006502.description: A team of two contestants try to "solve the slots" to get closer to winning a $250,000 jackpot.

0300000007.title: Farmer Wants a Wife
0300000007.description: This series follows four hard-working farmers in search of real, lasting love.

0300009728.title: The Gen Zone
0300009728.description: Hosted by Jhone Y. Lucas, this series keeps Generation Z politically awake and aware, featuring reactionary commentary about current events.

0300009127.title: Lisa Evers: Crime and Hip Hop
0300009127.description: New York crime and investigative reporter Lisa Evers probes the murders of three of the most significant hip hop artists of the last decade.

0300007100.title: Rising Up
0300007100.description: When you look back at the critical days last May and June which erupted into passionate protests and violence, you realize the match on the tinderbox was lit long before George Floyd. In Los Angeles, the roots of community frustration trace back to the Covid lockdown, the tragic death of Kobe Bryant, and even further, decades further, to the LA Riots. In this limited edition documentary series, in new interviews conducted coast to coast, we trace the timeline of the critical moments which led to a MOVEMENT never to be forgotten.

0300006283.title: Name That Tune
0300006283.description: Music-obsessed contestants face off in this exciting game show, as they try to identify popular songs with just a few notes for generous cash prizes.

0300008021.title: When Magic Shocked the World
0300008021.description: In 1991, Lakers legend Earvin “Magic” Johnson announced he had contracted the HIV virus, becoming an unlikely advocate for the deadly epidemic.

04890.title: American Heiress
04890.description: A rich debutant struggles to survive after a plane crash in the Guatemalan jungle, while her cruel brother at home tries to seize the family empire.

0300008367.title: Joe Millionaire: For Richer or Poorer
0300008367.description: Twenty women are faced with the age-old dilemma of choosing love or money while dating one prince and one pauper—without knowing which is which.

0300007785.title: Alter Ego
0300007785.description: In this musical competition show, undiscovered singers from all walks of life become the stars they always wanted to be, through their dream avatar.

0300005995.title: Beat Shazam
0300005995.description: Contestants race against the clock to identify hit songs and win $1 million dollars.

0300007667.title: FOX Fall Previews
0300007667.description: Here’s where you can get your first look at previews, bonus behind-the-scenes content, and more that will be coming to FOX this Fall of 2022.

0300006599.title: The Justice Report
0300006599.description: This weekly Fox affiliates report reveals stories of crime from all around the country, with a focus on live coverage and archival work.

0300005805.title: Fashion House
0300005805.description: A fashion industry titan protects her company and reputation from her ruthlessly ambitious rival who will do whatever it takes to win.

0300009737.title: Maino Presents: Kitchen Talk
0300009737.description: Musical artist Maino cooks up a great vibe for his friends in his kitchen, while having intriguing and thought-provoking conversations about life.

0300005214.title: LEGO Masters
0300005214.description: LEGO enthusiasts participate in a series of competitions that start with a single LEGO brick and culminate with inspiring, complex constructions.

0300009398.title: Miss Black USA
0300009398.description: Twenty diverse women from across the United States take the stage to compete for the title of Miss Black USA 2022.

0300008752.title: Domino Masters
0300008752.description: Teams of talented domino enthusiasts compete in a chain-reaction toppling tournament, and create mind-blowing, Rube-Goldberg-inspired masterpieces.

0300008168.title: World Pet Games
0300008168.description: Contestants place their pets in five hilarious, adorable events where winners get a donation to an animal charity made in their honor.

04717.title: Cosmos: A Spacetime Odyssey
04717.description: Join acclaimed astrophysicist Neil deGrasse Tyson on a journey through space and time in an effort to discover humanity’s place within the universe.

0300007927.title: The Cache
0300007927.description: Comedian and host Marcella Arguello is here with a curated clip-fest of some of the most hilarious and cringe-worthy wins and fails on the Web.

0300009741.title: Tracks & Tales
0300009741.description: From the minds of Greg Garvin and Shalimar Davis, Tracks and Tales is a reality series bringing viewers a concert celebration of music culture.

0300010052.title: Special Forces: World's Toughest Test
0300010052.description: This series follows celebrity contestants as they endure grueling challenges from the playbook of the actual Special Forces selection process.

04674.title: Desire
04674.description: Two brothers who get run out of town because of their passions end up in a love triangle that brings murder, betrayal and lust to a flashpoint.

0300000102.title: McMillan & Morrow
0300000102.description: Dr. Sean McMillan and Rich Morrow extract nuggets of virtue from people doing things they shouldn’t.

0300009201.title: Global Child
0300009201.description: Set off to amazing destinations with Augusto Valverde as he shares inspiring life lessons and the best experiences from his globetrotting travels.

0300005852.title: Watch Over Me
0300005852.description: A young bodyguard working for a ruthless industrialist gets involved with people in the unscrupulous business of researching  biological viruses.

0300007117.title: Crime Scene Kitchen
0300007117.description: Bakers must decode what type of dessert was made using just crumbs and a few elusive clues.

0300006250.title: The Masked Dancer
0300006250.description: Various celebrities compete against one another in a dance talent contest, while shrouded from head to toe in elaborate and whimsical costumes.

0300007793.title: Harry & Meghan: The Royals in Crisis
0300007793.description: Celebrities, moguls and social commentators weigh in on the couple's historic decision to step away from the Royal family and forge their own path.

0300007783.title: You Bet Your Life
0300007783.description: In a remake of Groucho Marx’s classic quiz show, Jay Leno adds funny headlines, goofy products, crazy lawsuits, and contestant interviews to the game.

0300009400.title: Person Place or Thing
0300009400.description: Contestants compete for a grand-prize vacation in a fast-paced and fun new show with a modern take on the game 20 questions.

0300010175.title: The Sharpton Sisters
0300010175.description: Meet the Sharpton sisters! Dominique and Ashley, Reverend Al Sharpton's daughters, bring their unique voices and friends to their new talk show.

0300009137.title: So You Think You Can Dance
0300009137.description: Skilled dancers showcase their talents in various dance styles while competing to be crowned America's favorite dancer.

0300006119.title: Celebrity Watch Party
0300006119.description: Pop-culture celebrities from Tyra Banks to Sharon Osbourne and JoJo Siwa watch and candidly comment on some of the best week’s TV with their family.

0300009157.title: MasterChef: Back to Win
0300009157.description: Returning contestants vie for the top prize as MasterChef re-opens its doors to some of the most memorable cooks in the competition’s history.

0300005163.title: The Masked Singer
0300005163.description: Celebrity performers, costumed to conceal their identities but dropping hints along the way, compete each week as one is eliminated and unmasked.
